{% extends "base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Realism Framework · Artifacts{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<h1>Realistic Enough for What?</h1>
<p>Companion artifacts to the paper <em>&ldquo;Realistic Enough for What? A
Multidimensional Framework for Evaluating Cyber Environments.&rdquo;</em> The framework
asks not whether an environment is realistic in general, but whether it has the realism
a given evaluation objective needs. Realism is decomposed into <strong>11 dimensions</strong>
(115 sub-dimensions), grouped by the part of an evaluation they affect.</p>

<h2>The 11 realism dimensions</h2>
{% for grp in groups %}
<section class="dim-group">
  <h3>{{ grp.name }}</h3>
  <p class="question">{{ grp.question }}</p>
  <dl>
  {% for d in grp.dims %}
    <dt>{{ dim_names[d] }}</dt>
    <dd>{{ dim_short[d] }}</dd>
  {% endfor %}
  </dl>
</section>
{% endfor %}

<h2>Explore</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="{{ rel }}use-cases/index.html">Use cases</a>: realism-requirement profiles for {{ n_uc }} evaluation objectives.</li>
  <li><a href="{{ rel }}environments/index.html">Environments</a>: the {{ n_env }}-environment coverage matrix and per-environment detail.</li>
  <li><a href="{{ rel }}scorecard.html">Scorecard</a>: our verdicts, and a tool to score an environment yourself.</li>
</ul>
{% endblock %}
